# Production Environment Configuration
#
# This file is a TEMPLATE for production environment variables.
# DO NOT put real production secrets in this file - it is committed to version control.
#
# PRODUCTION DEPLOYMENT:
#   Environment variables must be provided at Docker BUILD time using --build-arg flags.
#   Vite bundles these values into the static assets during the build process.
#
# METHODS FOR PROVIDING PRODUCTION VALUES:
#
#   1. Docker Build Arguments (recommended for CI/CD):
#      docker build \
#        --build-arg VITE_DUNGEON_MASTER_API_BASE_URL=https://your-api.run.app \
#        --build-arg VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=your-prod-key \
#        --build-arg VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your-prod-project.firebaseapp.com \
#        ... (all other Firebase variables) \
#        -t adventure-client:prod .
#
#   2. GitHub Actions Secrets:
#      Store secrets in repository Settings > Secrets and variables > Actions
#      Reference in workflow: ${{ secrets.FIREBASE_API_KEY }}
#
#   3. Google Secret Manager:
#      Store secrets in Secret Manager
#      Access in Cloud Build via secret references
#
# SECURITY NOTES:
#   - Use a separate Firebase project for production (not the same as dev/staging)
#   - Firebase API keys are meant to be public (access controlled by Security Rules)
#   - Never commit service account keys or backend secrets
#   - Rotate credentials periodically
#   - Add your Cloud Run domain to Firebase Authorized Domains
#
# See docs/firebase-setup.md for complete production setup instructions.

# ============================================================================
# API Base URLs (Production - Cloud Run Services)
# ============================================================================
# Your deployed backend service URLs on Google Cloud Run
# Example format: https://service-name-hash-uc.a.run.app

# Update these with your actual Cloud Run service URLs after deployment
VITE_DUNGEON_MASTER_API_BASE_URL=https://dungeon-master-api-prod-example.run.app
VITE_JOURNEY_LOG_API_BASE_URL=https://journey-log-api-prod-example.run.app

# ============================================================================
# Firebase Configuration (Production)
# ============================================================================
# CRITICAL: These must be provided via Docker build arguments or CI/CD secrets
# DO NOT fill in values here - use secure deployment methods instead
#
# Required values from Firebase Console > Project Settings > General > Your apps
# Use your PRODUCTION Firebase project (separate from dev/staging)

VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_MEASUREMENT_ID=

